quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,6,"Those who persist in disbelief, it is the same whether you warn them or not, they will not believe."
  2,7,"Allah has sealed their hearts and their hearing, and their sight is covered; and for them there will be a great punishment."
  2,8,"There are some people who say, “We believe in Allah and the Last Day,” whereas they are not believers."
  2,9,"They seek to deceive Allah and those who believe, while they deceive none but themselves, but they do not realize."
  2,10,"In their hearts is a sickness, and Allah increased their sickness, and they will have a painful punishment for their persistent lying."
  2,11,"When it is said to them, “Do not spread corruption in the land,” they say, “We are only reformers.”"
  2,12,"Indeed, it is they who spread corruption, but they do not realize it."
  2,13,"When it is said to them, “Believe as the people have believed,” they say, “Shall we believe as the fools have believed?” Indeed, it is they who are the fools, but they do not know."
  2,14,"When they meet those who believe, they say, “We believe.” But when they are alone with their evil ones, they say, “We are certainly with you; we were only mocking.”"
  2,15,"Allah will mock them and prolong them to wander blindly in their transgression."
  2,16,"They are those who purchased misguidance for guidance, but their trade was profitless, and they were not guided."